subContents.content: My name is Tom. Jack is my brother. He is an American. He is 15 years old. His home is near my school. He likes playing football and going shopping. He is a patient boy. His father and mother are both teachers. Last month he went to Paris for a vacation by plane. And he took many photos there. The Eiffel Tower is really wonderful.

question_boxs.description: 听下面一段录音，录音播放两遍。录音播放前你有10秒钟的阅题时间。录音播放后有两个问题。请根据所听到的问题和括号内的提示，选择正确的信息在8秒钟内口头回答。

content.contentDesc:
W: Who's your best friend, Jack?

M: Tina. We are both ten years old.

W: What do you think of Tina?

M: She is hard-working and patient. I like her very much.

W: Is she different from you in any way?

M: Well, I like playing basketball but she likes playing table tennis.

oralDict.contentDesc: ​How old is Tina?

answers.answer: Tina is ten years old.

subContents.content: What does Jack think of Tina?

sentencePatterns: Hard-working and patient. | <a> thinks <b> hard-working and patient. | <b> hard-working and patient.
oralDict.contentDesc: ​What does Jack think of Tina?

answers.answer: Jack thinks Tina is hard-working and patient.

content.contentDesc:
W: Hi, Bob. Is that Lucy? When did she get her hair cut?

M: Last week. The shoulder-length hair makes her more beautiful.

W: By the way, what do you like about her?

M: She is kind and friendly.

W: Does she like any sports?

M: She often plays table tennis with Jack.

subContents.content:
What does Lucy look like now?

(funny and friendly /shoulder-length hair. /tall and beautiful)

oralDict.contentDesc: What does Lucy look like now?

subContents.content:

(patient and friendly /long hair /kind and friendly)

sentencePatterns: <a> thinks <b> kind and friendly. | <b> kind and friendly.
oralDict.contentDesc: What does Bob like about Lucy?

answers.answer: He thinks Lucy is kind and friendly.

content.contentDesc:
M1: Hello, Dave. What do you like for breakfast?

M2: I like eggs and milk for breakfast. How about you, Jim?

M1: I like fruit for breakfast.

M2: What do you like for lunch?

M1: I have lunch at school with my friends. We all like hamburgers for lunch.

M2: I like hamburgers, too.

oralDict.contentDesc: ​Who likes fruit for breakfast?

subContents.content:
What do Dave and his good friends all like for lunch?

(Cakes./Fruit./Hamburgers.)

oralDict.contentDesc: ​My name is Alice. I have a new pen pal. Her name is Amy. She lives in England. Amy is a student. She goes to school on foot, because her home is not far from the school. Amy likes reading comic books and writing emails. Her father is an English teacher. He works in a school. He goes to work by car. He likes playing football and swimming.

answers.answer: Alice has a new pen pal. Her name is Amy. She lives in England. She goes to school on foot, because her home is not| isn’t far from the school. Amy likes reading comic books and writing emails. Her father is an English teacher. He likes playing football and swimming.
